<HEADLINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO LIGHT RAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A July 13 article on the performance of American rail systems erroneously 
quoted Sacramento's light rail ridership as 13,000 in contrast with projections 
of 50,000. 
</P>
<P>
Actually, in the final environmental impact statement, adopted just prior to 
the commitment to build the system, the federally approved weekday ridership 
forecast was 20,500. Current ridership is now over 21,000 daily boardings. 
Rush-hour trains are crowded; additional cars are under construction to expand 
capacity, and the system is generally considered a technical and political 
success. 
</P>
<P>
THOMAS G. MATOFF 
</P>
<P>
General Manager, Sacramento 
</P>
<P>
Regional Transit District 
</P>
</TEXT>
