<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIN TAXES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It seems we are always looking for something new to tax. 
</P>
<P>
We have the cigarette tax, the gas tax and the 5 cents a drink tax on alcohol 
coming soon. These taxes are tolerated because they are punishment for doing 
something bad. 
</P>
<P>
I have an idea for a tax that will pass the burden to another sinful segment. 
It is the dessert eaters. Let's tax every helping of dessert 25 cents. We might 
even tax desserts with raspberries a little more. I don't care much for 
raspberries. 
</P>
<P>
DON CALFEE 
</P>
<P>
Highland 
</P>
</TEXT>
