<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSIAL HEALTH SECRETARY LOUIS SULLIVAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have just read the interview with Sullivan for the third time. 
</P>
<P>
I was unable to believe what I was reading in his responses to the questions. 
</P>
<P>
Seat belts and no smoking. What a fantastic leadership position. Also, no salt. 
Also many small businesses would sink with the oppressive need to cover their 
employees with some insurance for health. Oh, I am in pain. 
</P>
<P>
National health insurance is offered worldwide in industrial nations, but not 
here. Why not? The federal government does certain things well; others that it 
doesn't . . . that we have fundamentally a system that has been very 
successful. 
</P>
<P>
Go tell that to the people that have to rely on the county and federal 
deliverance systems. They are in full failure. 
</P>
<P>
I've written to Dr. Sullivan. So what. I've now written The Times -- so what? 
</P>
<P>
I am at my wit's end to comprehend how far we have fallen as a nation of real 
compassion. 
</P>
<P>
Here's to Dr. Sullivan's charity hospitals. Woe is me. 
</P>
<P>
LORETTA CHILJIAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
