<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLEN RICE'S RUN LEADS VIKING VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CLEVELAND 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allen Rice raced 11 yards for a touchdown on a draw play with 4:27 left as the 
Minnesota Vikings beat the Cleveland Browns, 23-20, in an exhibition game 
Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
Rich Gannon, the Vikings' third quarterback, guided the 14-play, 73-yard 
winning drive on his first series. 
</P>
<P>
He set up the winning score by scrambling 18 yards on a third-and-20 play, then 
completing a five-yard pass to Andy Schillinger on fourth down. 
</P>
<P>
Rice, who missed most of last season with a knee injury, scored on the next 
play. 
</P>
<P>
Gannon completed six of 10 passes for 51 yards on the drive, which gave 
Minnesota its only second-half points. He later ran for 19 yards on the final 
series, helping the Vikings run out the clock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
