<HEADLINE>
<P>
3,000 IN JORDAN RAIL AGAINST WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AMMAN, Jordan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Muslim fundamentalists trampled and burned American, British and Israeli flags 
at a rally in Jordan on Sunday to show anger at Western military action in the 
Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
"Oh America, assemble your troops, tomorrow the soldiers of truth will crush 
you," chanted a mainly Palestinian crowd of 3,000 in the industrial town of 
Ruseifa, just outside Amman. 
</P>
<P>
Youths masked with checkered head cloths doused the flags with gasoline and set 
them on fire. The crowd surged forward, ripping at the blazing fragments of 
cloth. 
</P>
<P>
It was the latest in a series of rallies and protests in Jordan, where 
anti-Western feelings have exploded since U.S.-led forces arrived in Saudi 
Arabia to defend it against Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
The Muslim Brotherhood, which organized the Ruseifa rally, has not 
traditionally supported Iraqi President Saddam Hussein, who has crushed 
militant Shiite Muslim groups in Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
"Maybe Saddam has changed. We hope he is a good Muslim now," said Omar Obeid, a 
Brotherhood supporter in the crowd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
