<HEADLINE>
<P>
ART HISTORIAN FELIX KLEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wires Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BERN, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Felix Klee, a Swiss art historian and the son of artist Paul Klee, has died. 
Klee was 82 when he died on Aug. 13. 
</P>
<P>
In 1957, Klee published the diaries of his father and since 1963 had headed the 
Paul Klee Foundation. 
</P>
