<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 OF 18 CUBAN REFUGEES LEAVE SPANISH EMBASSY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAVANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two of the 18 Cubans who were sheltering at the Spanish Embassy in Havana gave 
themselves up to the authorities Saturday night, the Cuban Foreign Ministry 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
A ministry statement said that Ricardo Figueroa Laredo was taken to a hospital 
suffering from a stomach illness, while Felipe Nerey Fonseca was returned to 
his home. 
</P>
<P>
The two, who had managed to break into the embassy early last July 21 despite a 
heavy police guard, left voluntarily and without conditions, the statement 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Cuba has refused to allow any of the embassy refugees to leave the country but 
has promised they will not be punished if they give themselves up voluntarily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
