Cosby Show" begins. The shows go head-to-head for the first time at 8 p.m; both 
are repeats. . . . The English National Opera begins its 1990-91 season in 
London, made up exclusively of 20th-Century works, except for three Mozart 
operas chosen to mark the bicentenary of the composer's death. BETH KLEID 
