anniversary of the event, which began to help preserve Japanese culture. MITSU 
YASUKAWA / Los Angeles Times; Photo, (Southland Edition) Left, a street 
performer from Japan beats a drum and, . . . ; Photo, (A2) Sunday Afternoon at 
the Parade: A colorful parade through the streets of Little Tokyo launched a 
weeklong celebration of Japanese culture. Thousands watched costumed warlords 
on horseback and troupes of kimono-clad dancers as the 50th anniversary of the 
Nisei Week Festival began. B1 MARC YVES REGIS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
