<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CYA GRANTS TO AID 2 YOUTH PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Boys and Girls Club of Ventura and the Youth Connection of Camarillo are 
moving ahead with plans for expanding their facilities after winning grants of 
$75,000 and $750,000, respectively, from the California Youth Authority. 
</P>
<P>
The Boys and Girls Club provides care for disadvantaged children while offering 
recreation and enrichment activities for children ages 5 to 19. 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director Jane Goldschmidt said the money will be used to buy 
equipment and furnishings for a 15,000-square-foot expansion of its facility on 
Bristol Road, which will include a gymnasium and a computer learning center. 
</P>
<P>
The nonprofit Youth Connection was formed to coordinate and develop the Casa 
Pacifica project, a crisis care center able to house 85 to 110 abandoned, 
neglected or abused children. 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director Pamela Burke said the group's award will go toward financing 
about half of the center's administration facility on Esplanade Drive, which 
will include a toddler area, medical unit and nursery. 
</P>
<P>
Burke said construction is slated to begin in June, 1991, and will take about a 
year to complete. SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
