<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NINE BIRDIES BY DAVIS LOVE III CARRY HIM TO WIN IN COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Davis Love III, making nine birdies on a day when two players had double 
eagles, scored a three-point victory over Steve Pate, Peter Senior of Australia 
and Eduardo Romero of Argentina in the International golf tournament Sunday at 
Castle Pines Golf Club in Castle Rock, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
Only five double eagles were recorded in PGA Tour competition from 1987-1989, 
and there have been only two this season. 
</P>
<P>
Betsy King held off Beth Daniel by three shots to win the $400,000 Big Apple 
tournament. King eagled the par-five, 475-yard 18th hole for a 68 and a 72-hole 
score of 273 at the 6,209-yard Wykagyl Country Club at New Rochelle, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Rives McBee fired a final-round 68 to win the Seniors Showdown event at Jeremy 
Ranch by one stroke. McBee's 54-hole total of 14-under-par 202 was a tournament 
record. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Sutherland of Sacramento shot a five-under-par 67 to win the Queen Mary 
Open by two shots at Lakewood Country Club. Mike Miles of Cypress and Alan 
Tapie of Newport Beach tied for second. 
</P>
</TEXT>
