</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seymour Z. Rubenstein has been appointed president of Quality Systems Inc., a 
Tustin-based provider of computerized management systems to the health care 
industry. 
</P>
<P>
He succeeds Sheldon Razin, the company's founder, chairman and chief executive, 
who will remain in an overall leadership position at the company. 
</P>
<P>
Since joining the company in January, Rubenstein has served as the company's 
chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
