<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Lanie Jones and Frank Messina 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARK'N PAY: All-day parking rates at John Wayne Airport will climb from $12 to 
$14 if the county supervisors approve a county staff proposal Tuesday. The 
price would drop to $7 on the third day and the $1 hourly rate would remain the 
same. . . . The new prices are scheduled to go into effect on Sept. 16, when 
the Thomas F. Riley Terminal opens. . . . "We're providing more service for the 
money," an airport spokeswoman says. "People are getting covered parking, and 
it's very convenient." Lanie Jones and Frank Messina 
</P>
