PEARL BAILEY BURIAL SET IN PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jazz and blues singer Pearl Bailey will be buried in Philadelphia, where she 
spent much of her early career, her road manager said. 
</P>
<P>
"Her husband felt it was best since her family is here and she was raised up in 
Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
That's why we're having it here," said E. B. Smith, Bailey's manager for 23 
years. 
</P>
<P>
The funeral service will be held at 1 p.m. Thursday at the Deliverence 
Evangelistic Church in Philadelphia, followed by burial at the Rolling Green 
Memorial Park, where Bailey's mother and brother are buried. 
</P>
<P>
Smith said that it would be a "regular, plain funeral" but that people from as 
far away as California had already booked their flights to Philadelphia. He 
said he did not know how many people would turn out to say goodby to "Pearlie 
Mae." 
</P>
<P>
Song-and-dance man Cab Calloway had asked to be one of the six pallbearers, 
Smith said. And at least three of her managers, including Smith, also planned 
to help carry the coffin. 
</P>
<P>
Bailey, who at 72 had a history of heart trouble, collapsed Friday night at a 
Holiday Inn in Philadelphia's historic district, where she was recuperating 
from knee surgery performed last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
