<HEADLINE>
<P>
BROWN, MELVILLE OF U.S. WIN DOUBLES AT VOLVO INTERNATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW HAVEN, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Second-seeded Jeff Brown and Scott Melville defeated Goran Ivaniscevic and Petr 
Korda, 2-6, 7-5, 6-0 today to win the doubles final at the Volvo International 
tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The match was originally to be played Sunday but was postponed because of rain. 
</P>
<P>
Brown is from Flagler Beach, Fla., and Melville is from San Marino. Ivaniscevic 
and Korda are from Yugoslavia and Czechoslovakia, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Derrick Rostagno defeated Todd Woodbridge, 6-3, 6-3 to win the singles final 
Sunday in a match delayed five hours and 40 minutes by rain. 
</P>
<P>
In Italy, unseeded Cedric Pioline of France fought back from a first-set loss 
today to beat Sweden's Lars Jonsson, 5-7, 6-3, 6-2, in the first round of the 
ATP San Marino Open. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round action, Paul Vojtisek of West Germany defeated Nuno 
Marques of Portugal, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Top seeded Guillermo Perez-Roldan of Argentina and second-seeded Austrian Horst 
Skoff begin first-round action Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Perez-Roldan will play Italy's Massimo Cierro while Skoff takes on Federico 
Mordegan of Italy. 
</P>
