<TEXT>
<P>
Mark Martin's victory in the Champion Spark Plug 400 at Michigan International 
Speedway extended his lead in the NASCAR Winston Cup standings to 48 points 
over second-place Dale Earnhardt. 
</P>
<P>
Martin entered Sunday's race with a nine-point lead and now has 2,854 points to 
2,806 for three-time Winston Cup champion Earnhardt, who finished eighth at 
Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
Geoff Bodine finished seventh and now trails Martin by 154 points with 2,700. 
</P>
<P>
